Meanwhile, writing in his weekly open letter to the public, President Cyril Ramaphosa said South Africa was in a third wave of Covid-19 infections. He warned that all citizens would need to do their part to help limit the toll, including adhering to lockdown regulations and, if they could, going beyond the gazetted requirements.Ramaphosa said â€œThe climb in new cases has been extraordinarily rapid and steep over the past few weeks. The number of daily new cases jumped from below 800 in early April to over 13 000 in the past week.â€œIn other words, it increased more than fifteen-fold from the last low point.Once again, we have to avoid social gatherings of all kinds, whether for family, friends, business or recreation.â€ rudolph.nkgadima@africannewsagency.com